# Code standards

## TypeScript
- Strict mode is on. No `any`. Use `unknown` + narrowing when the type is genuinely unknown.
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for object shapes. Use `interface` only for things meant to be extended.
- All async functions must have explicit return types: `async function foo(): Promise<Bar>`.
- Never use non-null assertion (`!`) on values that could realistically be null at runtime.

## Naming
- Files: `kebab-case.ts` / `kebab-case.tsx` (enforced by `unicorn/filename-case` ‚Äî see `09-tooling-feedback`)
- Components: `PascalCase`
- Hooks: `camelCase` prefixed with `use`
- Server actions: `camelCase` prefixed with the verb (`createX`, `updateX`, `deleteX`)
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`
- DB table names: `snake_case`

## File size
- ~200 lines per file, ~80 lines per function (enforced as `warn` by ESLint ‚Äî see `09-tooling-feedback`).
- Cursor only reads the first ~250 lines of a file before deciding whether to read more. Long files hurt both humans and agents.
- One component per file. Co-locate types and local hooks only if they aren't reused.

## Error handling
- Never swallow errors silently. Always log or surface them.
- Server actions return `{ data, error }` ‚Äî never throw from a server action called by a Client Component.
- Route handlers return `{ error: string }` with the appropriate HTTP status on failure.
- Always check the `error` field on DB calls before using `data`.

## Definition of done
You are not done until the code commits cleanly. Pre-commit hooks run TypeScript checks and ESLint ‚Äî a successful commit is the definition of done. Never use `--no-verify`.

## Do not install
- ‚ùå `axios` ‚Äî use `fetch`
- ‚ùå `moment` / `dayjs` ‚Äî use `date-fns`
- ‚ùå `lodash` ‚Äî use native JS or a focused utility
- ‚ùå `react-query` / `swr` in Next.js App Router unless explicitly required ‚Äî prefer Server Components + server actions

## Never do
- ‚ùå `@ts-ignore` or `@ts-expect-error` without an explanatory comment
- ‚ùå Leave `console.log` in committed code
- ‚ùå Create `-v2`, `-new`, `-fixed`, or `-copy` versions of files ‚Äî rename or replace
- ‚ùå Leave dead code or unused imports
- ‚ùå Use `any` ‚Äî use `unknown` + type narrowing

## Imports
- Use path aliases (`@/components/...`, `@/lib/...`) ‚Äî never relative `../../` imports.
- Group: external packages ‚Üí internal `@/lib` ‚Üí internal `@/components` ‚Üí local. Blank line between groups. (Enforced by `perfectionist/sort-imports`.)
